{"questionId":"33478197","questionHtml":"<p>Consider the function <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>log</mi><mn>10</mn></msub><mo> </mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>3</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mi>r</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>r</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>, where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℝ</mi></math>.</p>\n<p>Find the possible values of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>r</mi></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>METHOD 1</strong></p>\n<p>recognition that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mi>r</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>r</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></math> must be greater than zero (seen anywhere)<em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R</strong><strong>1</strong></em></p>\n<p>(discriminant&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo></math>) <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mi>r</mi></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mfenced><mn>3</mn></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><mi>r</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>12</mn><mi>r</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>24</mn><mo>)</mo></math> (seen anywhere)<em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>53589</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mo>)</mo></math>&nbsp; AND&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>9</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>46410</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mo>)</mo></math> (seen anywhere)<em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>recognition that discriminant of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mi>r</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>r</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></math> is less than zero<em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>54</mn><mo>&lt;</mo><mi>r</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>46</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mo>&lt;</mo><mi>r</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mo>)</mo></math> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note</strong>: Accept <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>54</mn><mo>≤</mo><mi>r</mi><mo>≤</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>46</mn></math>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 2</strong></p>\n<p>recognition that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mi>r</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>r</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></math> must be greater than zero (seen anywhere)<em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R</strong><strong>1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p>minimum when&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>r</mi><mn>6</mn></mfrac><mo>⇒</mo><mo>(</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>)</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>3</mn><msup><mfenced><mfrac><mi>r</mi><mn>6</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mi>r</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mi>r</mi><mn>6</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mi>r</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>)</mo></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>(A1)</strong></em><strong><br></strong></p>\n<p>attempt to solve their inequality for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi></math> (must be in terms of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>r</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>)<em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>⇒</mo><mi>r</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac></math></strong></em> &nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>⇒</mo><mi>r</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac></math> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; (A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempt to find local minumum AND local maximum of <em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>r</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac></math> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; (M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>THEN</strong></p>\n<p><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mi>r</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mo>)</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>53589</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mo>)</mo></math> &nbsp;</strong>AND&nbsp; <strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mi>r</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mo>)</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>46410</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mo>)</mo></math></strong> (seen anywhere)<em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>(A1)</strong></em><strong><br></strong></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>54</mn><mo>&lt;</mo><mi>r</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>46</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mo>&lt;</mo><mi>r</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mo>)</mo></math> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note</strong>: Accept <em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>54</mn><mo>≤</mo><mi>r</mi><mo>≤</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>46</mn></math>.</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[5 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"33478197","referenceCode":"24N.2.SL.TZ1.6","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Consider the function hx=log10 3x2-rx+r-2, where x∈ℝ. Find the possible values of r.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"6","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 5]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.7—Solutions of quadratic equations and inequalities, discriminant and nature of roots","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.5—Intro to logs"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}